      "name": "Literature synthesis: hemolysis baseline from prior CFD pump studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of eight prior peer-reviewed CFD hemolysis studies covering centrifugal and axial blood pumps (2005–2022). Aggregates power-law damage model coefficients, reported GCI values, and experimental correlation ranges from FDA benchmark exercises. Provides the prior expectation for acceptable hemolysis prediction accuracy and informs the RH < 1 acceptance threshold used in the primary validation. This node represents consolidated domain knowledge drawn from the broader hemolysis modelling literature and is a key epistemic anchor for the credibility claim."
